            <div class="testimonials-v3-title">
              <p>Sandie</p>
              <span>Sandie Kisting, Indigo Healing, Middleton Wi</span>
            </div>
            <p>I want to first start out by saying that I wasn’t going to attend this retreat. It was a facebook event hosted by a company that I knew nothing about. However, the closer it got to the event, the more I saw it’s message pop up on Facebook. So, I finally looked into the event.The event was being held in the Midwest, in Michigan, close to my home. There were all types of indicators that I should attend. First the Facebook post kept popping up every time I was online.Next there was contact via facebook of another person in the area attending the workshop. He was in the Midwest. I finally called for more information on the number listed in the event. It was there that I first talked with Wendy Jo.From there a series of events took place..I started a new job in my field, of massage, it allowed me to be able to afford the retreat event. Next Wendy Jo explained that other quality professionals in my field would be in attendance including Jean Paul Lacroix and Julien Lacroix, both specialist in the field of healing as well as Shamanism. Wendy Jo and I communicated over the phone for the next few days as well as chat.I was undecided about attending the event right up until the week before. I decided by Wendy Jo’s persistence that it would be a life changing experience. Wendy said she couldn’t explain it but I wouldn’t be disappointed. The next several days I was contacted through staff and other attendees and briefly met for the first time on chat.Wendy felt overwhelmed but I assured her that she would be able to get enough attendees and then we would finally meet. I continued to seek other therapists to attend with me on short notice, but then Wendy Jo phthreed to say the class was full for attendees.I ventured away from my home state of Wisconsin and decided to drive the almost 5 hour adventure. It was so last minute so I looked at the email, threw together the items on the list and headed to Michigan. It had been almost 10 years since I went out of state for a workshop, especially on my own. For good measure, I took extra cash with me in case of emergencies, something I don’t always have on hand.Each step of my adventure was blessed with divine guidance. For example, I usually map out my drive before I embark on my journey. I did this. I decided to stop at the Wisconsin-Illinois border at the rest area to get a current Illinois map. This is when I mentithreed to the staff behind the counter that I was headed towards the Chicago bypass. The woman advised me to take an alternate route south, twenty minutes out of my way, but I’d avoid the congestion in Chicago due to the Stanley Cup winner and celebration for the Chiefs. So I took her instructions, my new map and detoured south. Turns out I have driven this road many times headed to Missouri for family reunions.As I headed towards Illinois 80, I realized that I would pass through Gary, Indiana as well as Michigan.So I drove Wisconsin, Illinois, Indiana, Michigan to get to retreat. A first for me so I took the time to stop along the way and enjoy the scenery. It delayed my arrival, but after all, I was on an adventure. So I eventually reached my retreat destination. I knew it was going to be great when I pulled up to Ronora and realized it was the perfect place for a retreat. Quiet, hidden, calm, peaceful. Little did I know that my journey was just beginning.</p><h4>~Arrival Day~</h4><p>I drove up to the lodge and located the house where we would be staying. It was two story with tons of rooms and apparently lots of new friends I needed to meet. I went inside and looked around and that’s where I met my first of many new friends. We introduced ourselves and chatted a bit and then gathered our things from the car to the house where we would be staying.Shortly thereafter, several other participants came in and we introduced ourselves and started to greet each other. There was time before we formally gathered and after we were “moved in”, I explored the rest of the grounds. There was a lake, a meditation house, other cabins, tennis courts, nature trails and my favorite the swing set. I couldn’t resist. I jumped into a swing and began to fly as high as I could. After a few minutes of release, my long car drive behind me, I stopped and looked up. I noticed the sticker on the swing that said “No adults allowed. No three over 300 lbs..Kids under 8 years” I chuckled as I realized I’d broken a rule at camp and I wasn’t even there for 30 minutes. I quietly stepped away from the swings and headed back to the house to meet up with the others. We then proceeded to the big hall for opening ceremonies.</p><h4>~Week of Learning~</h4><p>With each new day, I discovered more about my personal self. Issues that I had thought were dealt with were obviously hidden under the surface. With each new technique or breathing exercise or massage, my body and mind released more and more. Every day brought a new idea or thought process. Each day taught us how to be optimally well so we could work with our clients.I am open to new ideas and while some of the techniques forced me out of my comfort zthree, the entire experience truly changed my life. Wendy Jo was right. I’ve made some amazing new friends, learned more about myself, have learned new techniques of people management as well as self management. The retreat made me realize that there is still an entire world out there to explore and enjoy.The staff was top notch. They were very professional and the workshops always began on time. There was a reflection session each day and a sharing session if you chose to participate. Both were very beneficial because these sessions taught all of us how to communicate and how to listen better. We learned about trials and triumphs as well as ways to learn from our mistakes.The workshops were intense sessions and we learned much. They were organized and always were relevant to the lessons being taught. If there were questions, they were addressed efficiently and truthfully. The experience of sharing with others only made the retreat more impressive.The other attendees were also a great resource for the workshop. We all brought our individual talents and abilities to add to the retreat. Each of us had unique professions and contributed to the overall process of learning. We shared techniques, stories of personal growth and achievement as well as gaining friendships that last. We have also stayed in contact since the retreat since we are now a great support network for each other.I can truly say that Wendy Jo was correct. This was definitely a life changing adventure! Words can never truly express what this retreat has dthree for me both personally and professionally and I thank God everyday that He sent me to find all of them.I encourage you to attend our next retreat because it will be life changing and it will be a forever memory filled with compassion,fun, love, new ideas, great people and tons of new friends. Hope to see you there!</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
