            <div class="testimonials-v3-title">
              <p>Christine</p>
              <span>French Translator, 1st Cocoon-US Retreat </span>
            </div>
              <p>My name is Christine Newton. I’m writing to share my story with you. It’s a little different from everyone else’s because I attended the workshop with the purpose of using my French language skills outside the classroom. This essentially was a job opportunity for me at a great location, West side of the state near the Lake Michigan. <br>Yah hoo! I kept calling for the translation job that was forwarded to me through French-American Chamber of Commerce but no reply.Finally when I had given up, I got the call from Wendy. She was worried about finding the right person for the translation position. It was not a typical 9 to 5 job. She wanted me to understand that it would be more of an intimate personal setting, where we were together during instruction time and meal times. I would translate as needed.As for my part, I had one concern, I ‘m a Christian and I didn’t want this to be some evil spirit thing.<br> Additionally, I had no background in massage healing but was willing to learn. Wendy assured me that everything would be in alignment with my faith and not to worry otherwise she wouldn't be promoting it.Once I felt I could accept the translation job, I packed and was on the road the next morning.Upon my arrival, I met with the members of the team, Wendy, Jean-Paul, Julian and Airgyro, and I was able to get settled in to my quarters. Then we reviewed the itinerary for each day.It was decided that all translations would be in the moment or live. Soon thereafter, the various participants trickled in then towards 5 o’clock we all sat in a circle and were able to make formal introductions and go over basic rules.This was a diverse group, ages 19-60’s. Most had had some experience with giving massage and or meditation. They were all open to learning and growing in this new technique. The team also established rules of safety such as: no picture taking, what is said here stays private. <br>If anyone was uncomfortable with anything, they just needed to say so and nothing was compulsory. Nothing sexual would be associated with healing massage, nor judging others or their reactions. The stage was set for a safe environment.To give a general picture of our week, most activities started off with the participants having to relax and shut off their thinking. I would translate the words of Jean-Paul as he guided the exercises. Background music was played.Besides being a translator, I had the privilege of being an observer and would notice the various degrees to which people were or were not able to let go. In one breathing exercise, I could witness participants working through their subconscious issues. A few were really arching their backs and crying and screaming out their pain. I remember thinking “ Wow, I never realized how much pain people carry inside, particularly victims of unresloved trauma.”I could "see" it on their outside appearances, but it was worse to see how deeply it was embedded in their bodies.As the exercises were practiced, the brokenness of the participants manifested itself in many different overt behaviors such as: fingers tight and frozen, shaking, running in place, various sounds coming from their mouths.Others went into expressing themselves as animals, such as a bird soaring, or crawling on the floor reconnecting with nature and their individual power.Others had unresolved childhood issues. <br>Jean-Paul would have me whisper positive words into their ears, such as “You are loved my daughter.”Others were encouraged to, "let go, stay with that feeling, you are doing well, yes, yes.....Then others were calm, placid, and smiling in happy places with arms letting loose in dance movements as if in a beautiful dream.After such exercises, we would go back into the circle and discuss what they felt after this particular activity.I would translate their testimonies into French for our French Cocoon team. It was their 1st time visit to the United States and we worked through some minor cultural barriers and connected at a soul level.Wendy experienced Cocoon in Greece and was guided to let others experience it in the United States.I was surprised how natural the live translation came to me as it felt strained when I attempted to pre-script.While translating some of the more difficult testimonies, I would fight to hold back my own tears. Hearing how a violent rape led a participant feeling as if they had lost control and power over their life. This hurt my heart to hear let alone translate to the group.Again, there was no judgment. The participants were like children and the safe space facilitated them to be vulnerable.<h4>~The Shift ~</h4>Through this process, I began to see the participants differently. I began to see them through their hearts. There was no judgment, fat, skinny, young or old.ALL of the body shapes and sizes were beautiful! No one was more or less than anyone else. Respect and love excuded the environment.Towards the 4th day, some began to notice that I was getting frustrated. I was watching this transformational process and witnessing the participants gain healing. Yet, I was not because of my position as the Translator.This is when Jean-Paul offered a healing Cocoon massage to me, if I wanted one.At this point, I knew I needed this, but I was afraid! What if I couldn’t relax my body enough? What if I farted or something? Worried and stuck "in my head". I’m such a thinker.After 28 years of teaching and two master’s degrees, it’s hard for me to stop thinking.On the last day, as the participants practiced on each other, I received a Cocoon healing massage from Jean-Paul.I rested myself with my eyes closed. As the massage began, I decided to just let things go where they went. Let go with no expectations.After some time, the breathing helped me get "out of my head". <br>I don’t know how long it was into the massage when very energtically driven things began to involuntarily occur. When certain parts of my body was touched, I could feel energy pulsing through my body. I had involuntary arm and hand flagellations, and I had a clear vision of a white flower field.As Jean-Paul pressed on kidney stone five, a pressure point located on the base of my foot, a great surge of energy came up my entire body as I screamed out releasing subconsciois emotional pain. My body had been holding this for who knows how long yet this molality reached it in less than two hours. I yelled as loud as I could and then held my yell for as far and long as I could until I could no more…. and then I 'let it go"….At another point, Jean–Paul was, holding and rocking me like he was my mom. I started to talk as if I was talking to her. I felt so much love from her and wanted to continue rocking. It was safe as in Cocoon.He also strategically placed my feet on ground and held them. Suddenly, I felt a sensation of being centered and fully grounded.Once my 2-hour massage was over, I transitioned out if it slowly. I felt so relaxed and content.<h4>Then something WONDERFUL happened:</h4>I couldn’t stop smiling.I was happy, genuinely gut-happy like a child.I felt as if the thicket and prickles of pain in my heart had been removed and now the space in there was smooth and no longer taken up by those feelings.I felt more energy and space to take in love or give love out. I had vision for things I want to do with my life in the near future.This is healing, not a"mind" thing at all. The breathwork, meditation, massage ams conscious touch principles are scientifically supported as effective alternative healing modalities.I am eager and excited, as this unanticipated, yet divenly scripted healing and liberating process continues.The alternative breathwork, massage, meditation and conscious touch modalities that Wendy Jo is avidly promoting as well as practicing personally are beyond words.Accepting this opportunity, required blind faith and a big leap. I will receive lifelong dividends from it. <br>Wendy exudes passion and gratitude while "Angels Secure the Perimeter"and miracles manifest.I pray that anyone who desires to participate in events coordinated by UBU TODAY that barriers are eliminated.I believe that God gave me this opportunity, as a gift for my own healing, because I was not seeking it at all.What was first taken as a "translation job opportunity" turned into a "life changing experience".This is just the beginning!
              <h4>B. T. W. It’s a month later and I am still smiling!</h4></p> 
          </li>
