            <p>My name is Jimi Merk and I am a natural healing practitioner of many modalities with a focus in Shamanic healing techniques. I am a psychic medical intuitive as well as a medium. I have been working with people in holistic arts and medicine for over 12 years and have helped people all across America. I have a patin for helping people to Shine and started my wellness studio 9 years ago called Shine Your Light Wellness. I help all ages of clientele with all types of clinical and psychological issues. I help people to rehabilitate the body, mind, and spirit as well as teach my clients to heal themselves and others. I love to teach and travel the country continually teaching healing, intuitive ability development, spirituality, and astrophysics.<br>I was looking for something powerful to grow in my practice as well as to help others with when I found out about the Cocoon retreat and study in Michigan. It was through Wendy Jo, on Facebook, that I was given the opportunity to learn this unique combination of Dance movement work, powerful breathing Shamanic meditations, and nurturing with gentle Tantra healing massage. I love to Dance so the more movement and dancing the better as far as Im concerned. It is a wonderful way to connect to the body and your environment. The Dance helped us to place ourself in that vulnerable space to help with tearing down of walls of ego and to help people express through the creative self. Dance is fun and physical so it also helps release stress that is trapped in the body and gets the blood flowing.<br>The Deep breathing Kundalini meditation that we learned and experienced was perfect for forcing the release of emotional stress and pain. I have studied similar deep breathing meditations that are all very functional in pulling up emotional trauma and fear so that it can be released from the body, heart, and mind. This extensive meditation is unique because it involves holding space as well as pressure point and energy hands on healing techniques to assist in the healing journey of the participant. I loved how fast the response to the breathing and movement allowed for speedy release and healing. It was a very powerful experience and tremendously healing even for me as a seasoned practitioner and teacher. I connected with all of my guidance, animal spirits, and everything in the universe, It was a very powerful experience for me personally.<br>The Tantra massage was the perfect addition to this series as it was so incredibly nurturing and approached with a loving and gentle manner. After such movement with the dancing and the exhaustion of the deep rooted healing meditations this was exactly what our Bodies, hearts, and minds needed. By massaging we were squeezing out any remaining tension held in the body and allowing for better blood flow and rejuvenation. It was revealing as we were also nude while the massage was taking place which again allows us to let down ego and over protected boundaries that keep us from being comfortable with self. It also allows for ease of connection between practitioner and participant, both parties are vulnerable in the space and both hold respect and humility for each other. The tantra massage is wonderful las it is completed with lovely oils to aid in the healing and is done very slowly as to not disturb the mind and emotion as they are releasing more stress, fear, and pain. I absolutely loved this part of the retreat and study and have already enjoyed the healing power of the tantra massage with my clients and friends.<br>Overall Cocoon made an amazing 5 day workshop to experience with and learn. It will not only help me grow as a professional healing practitioner but will help me progress in my own personal practice permanently. I really appreciated my time with Jean Pauls team and look forward to learning more.<br>I feel that every practioner in the healing arts should experience this practice and the combination of modalities that are used! Shine<br><small>JIMI MERK</small></p>
